cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper deals with mathematical morphology operators that are adaptive to illumination changes, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new set of mathematical morphology operators, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Mathematical Software). The paper also discusses the Logarithmic Image Processing (LIP) model, which is based on the physics of acquisition, and involves signal processing and information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely category. The paper also presents results on simulated and real images, which involves image processing and analysis, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses pattern recognition, which falls under the category of cs.GR (Graphics).
